commands/addbiscuitentry.title: addbiscuitentry
commands/addbiscuitentry.content:
bb!addbiscuitentry <user>

This command adds a specified user to the Biscuits database. If a user is in this database, they can use BotBiscuit's economy. This command is really only a last resort for helping people who can't fingure out how to make an account by themselves - BotBiscuit automaatically creates accounts for people when they join a server with BotBiscuit in, and people can also use bb!createbiscuitaccount to create an account for themselves.

Usage

bb!addbiscuitentry <user> where <user> is either a mention or a user ID.

Aliases

bb!abe

Permission Level

Admin

Example

commands/biscuits.title: biscuits
commands/biscuits.content:
bb!biscuits [user]

This command shows you either your own biscuit balance or the biscuit balance of any other user.

Usage

bb!biscuits [user] where [user] is an optional mention or user ID.

Aliases

bb!b bb!balance

Permission Level

Verified

Example

commands/buy.title: buy
commands/buy.content:
bb!buy <path>

This command allows you to use your biscuits to buy items from the shop.

Usage

bb!buy <path> where <path> is the path in the shop of the item you wish to buy. When viewing an item in the shop, a list of numbers will appear next to the name of the item (as shown below) - this is the path.

Permission Level

Verified

Example

commands/createbiscuitaccount.title: createbiscuitaccount
commands/createbiscuitaccount.content:
bb!createbiscuitaccount

This command creates an entry in the biscuits database for the person using it.

Usage

bb!createbiscuitaccount

Permission Level

Verified

Example

commands/daily.title: daily
commands/daily.content:
bb!daily

This command gives you your daily biscuits. You can use it once every 24 hours.

Usage

bb!daily

Permission Level

Verified

Example

commands/givebiscuits.title: givebiscuits
commands/givebiscuits.content:
bb!givebiscuits <user> <number>

This command allows you to give biscuits to other users.

Usage

bb!givebiscuits <user> <number> where <user> is a mention or user ID and <number> is a positive integer less than your biscuit balance.

Aliases

bb!gb

Permission Level

Verified

Example

commands/shop.title: shop
commands/shop.content:
bb!shop <path>

This command lets you see all the items currently on sale in the shop.

Usage

bb!shop <path> where <path> is the path to the item or category you want to view. Each item or category has a number next to it when you view the shop - if you add a space and then that number to the end of the path you are currently viewing, you will view that item/category.

Permission Level

Verified

Example

commands/ban.title: ban
commands/ban.content:
bb!ban <user> <time> [reason]

This command bans the specified user from the server the command is used in for the amount of time specified. It also logs this ban in the infractions database.

Usage

bb!ban <user> <time> [reason] where <user> is a user ID or mention, <time> is the period of time to ban the user for, and [reason] is an optional reason for the ban.

Permission Level

Admin

Example

commands/infractions.title: infractions
commands/infractions.content:
bb!infractions <user>

This command lets you see all unpardoned infractions (bans, kicks, warns etc) a user has against them.

Usage

bb!infractions <user> where <user> is a mention or user ID.

Permission Level

Moderator
